57.1	Nikki_Giovanni	Nikki Giovanni	Yolande Cornelia "Nikki" Giovanni (born June 7, 1943) is an American poet, writer, commentator, activist, and educator. Her primary focus is on the individual and the power one has to make a difference in oneself and in the lives of others. Giovanniâ€™s poetry expresses strong racial pride, respect for family, and her own experiences as a daughter, a civil rights activist, and a mother. She is currently a distinguished professor of English at Virginia Tech.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Nikki_Giovanni_speaking_at_Emory_University_2008.jpg/200px-Nikki_Giovanni_speaking_at_Emory_University_2008.jpg
